Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy applies to the vvcmcopd app (hereafter referred to as the "Application") for mobile devices, developed by Vasai-Virar City Municipal Corporation (hereafter referred to as the "Service Provider"). The Application is provided as a free service and is intended for use "AS IS."

Information Collection and Use

The Application collects certain information when you download and use it. This may include:

Your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address.

The pages of the Application that you visit, including the time, date, and duration of your visit.

The total time spent on the Application.

The operating system of your mobile device.

The Application does not collect precise location data from your mobile device.

The Service Provider may use the collected information to communicate with you occasionally, providing important updates, required notices, and marketing promotions.

For an improved experience while using the Application, the Service Provider may require certain personally identifiable information. However, no personally identifiable information is explicitly collected unless voluntarily provided by the user. The collected information will be retained and used as described in this Privacy Policy.

Third-Party Access

Only aggregated and anonymized data is periodically shared with external services to enhance the Application and improve service quality. The Service Provider may share collected data with third parties under the conditions outlined in this policy.

Please note that the Application utilizes third-party services that have their own Privacy Policies regarding data handling. Below is a link to the Privacy Policy of the third-party service provider used by the Application:

Google Play Services

The Service Provider may disclose collected information in the following cases:

When required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena or similar legal process.

When necessary to protect rights, ensure user safety, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.

With trusted service providers who work on behalf of the Service Provider, provided they agree to adhere to the rules set forth in this Privacy Policy.

Opt-Out Rights

Users can stop the collection of information by uninstalling the Application. The standard uninstall process available on mobile devices or application marketplaces can be used to remove the Application.

Data Retention Policy

The Service Provider will retain user-provided data for as long as the user continues to use the Application and for a reasonable period thereafter. If you wish to request the deletion of your data collected via the Application, please contact the Service Provider at mycare@dssworld.in, and your request will be addressed within a reasonable timeframe.

Children's Privacy

The Service Provider does not knowingly collect or solicit data from children under the age of 13. The Application is not intended for use by children under 13 years of age.

If it is discovered that a child under 13 has provided personal information, such data will be immediately deleted from the Service Providerâ€™s records. If you are a parent or guardian and become aware that your child has provided personal information, please contact the Service Provider at mycare@dssworld.in so appropriate action can be taken.

Security

The Service Provider takes appropriate security measures to protect your information, employing physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to maintain data confidentiality and prevent unauthorized access.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically for various reasons. Any changes will be posted on this page, and it is recommended that users review this Privacy Policy regularly to stay informed. Continued use of the Application after any modifications to the policy constitutes acceptance of those changes.

This Privacy Policy is effective as of March 3, 2025.

Your Consent

By using the Application, you consent to the collection and use of your information as outlined in this Privacy Policy.

